<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=57&amp;p=11800#p11800"><![CDATA[
Are you sure the mirroring connection is set up right?  The MMC3 should have a "CIRAM A10" pin which controls the PPU mirroring.  A TLSROM board probably doesn't have the pin connected to anything, so make sure that pin goes to the CIRAM A10 pin on the cart edge.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=360">dvdmth</a> — Tue Apr 11, 2006 8:42 am</p><hr />
